  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency assistance to crisis affected communities of Central African Republic &#x2013; International Medical Corps UK (IMC) headed consortium with Save the Children Fund, Mentor Initiative, Oxfam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">International Medical Corps, The Save the Children Fund, MENTOR Initiative, and Oxfam will implement an action to respond to the health needs of conflict affected populations across four prefectures in Central African Republic (CAR). In the targeted prefectures, partners will provide support to health facilities to increase their capacity to respond to emergency health and nutrition needs, including the provision of services/referrals to survivors of Gender Based Violence (GBV). In addition, community health agents will work to build local communities&apos; capacity to support in prevention and treatment of most common morbidities and malnutrition.;</narrative>
  </description>
